@danmulholland1634 Numbers doesn't equal quality, Lord of The Rings is better than Avatar and yada yada yada.

You're also not taken in to account the population growth, inflation, hype from a legendary status that has been growing and just more people going to the cinema at that time than when 1,2 and 3 came out.  

It's not an opinion either. It's based on objective rules of the craft, human biology and society. Almost nobody talks about Toy Story 4 anymore unless it's in a bad light. Same can't be said for the other three movies. So obviously there is something with it that just didn't stick and blend into film culture.
